Culture methods to evaluate central venous catheter sepsis.
 Sepsis is a frequent complication of central venous catheters, but the diagnosis of catheter sepsis is not always clear-cut.
 A variety of culture methods is available to determine catheter-related septicemia.
 Each method has advantages and disadvantages for the clinician to consider.
 This article reviews qualitative, quantitative, and other culture methods applicable to both blood and the device.
